name: MoodDisorders
title: Mood Disorders
description: SNOMED CT intensional (rule-based) value set for defining mood disorder diagnoses, available for a range of potential uses including problem-oriented views of relevant clinical information, clinical decision support rules, electronic patient registries, and data analytics.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Broad grouper of diagnosis concepts for mood disorders.),(Data Element Scope: Employs SNOMED CT concept hierarchies primarily in the Disorder (Clinical finding) branch, though some can be in the Situation with Explicit Context branch or the Procedure branch.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes all types of depression (primary or secondary to another condition, chronic or episodic), bipolar disorder, mood disorders with psychotic symptoms, dysthymia, and transient postpartum mood disturbance.),(Exclusion Criteria: (Currently contains no excluded concepts))
